when upgrading some things might break until restart

## kernel modules

Kernel modules are stored in a folder, that is named based on the version of the linux kernel, that they are for.
When updating, pacman moves the kernel modules to the new folder and/or replaces them by a new version (not 100% factual).
This means that loading new kernel modules fails.

## usb-sticks
When pluging in an usb-stick for the first time after booting, a kernel module is loaded.
This means, that a reboot is required before usb-sticks start working again.

## valgrind
Valgrind failes if gcc or something is updated.
